cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this dataset or its FAIR metadata, please cite both the original publication and this metadata implementation."
title: "BE1 Benchmark Dataset for Single-Cell RNA Sequencing: Controlled Cancer Heterogeneity"
abstract: "A 10XGenomics single-cell RNA sequencing benchmark dataset providing a controlled heterogeneous environment using seven lung cancer cell lines characterised by the expression of seven different driver genes (EGFR, ALK, MET, ERBB2, KRAS, BRAF, ROS1). The dataset includes 29,528 cells from PC9 (EGFR Del19), A549 (KRAS G12S), NCI-H596 (MET Del14), NCI-H1395 (BRAF G469A), DV90 (ERBB2 V842I), HCC78 (ROS1 fusion), CCL.185-IG (ALK fusion) cell lines, plus PBMC control. This resource enables the development and validation of computational methodologies for analysing cancer heterogeneity through scRNA-seq. FAIR-compliant metadata following Single Cell Schema v0.4 (Darwin Core extension) with enhanced interoperability and machine learning readiness."
authors:
  - family-names: "ELIXIR"
    given-names: "Single Cell Omics Community"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1825-0097"
    affiliation: "ELIXIR Europe"
    email: "single-cell-omics@elixir-europe.org"

